Company\
\
I worked at the company \cf5 \cb3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
libs Industrielle Berufslehren Schweiz\cf0 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0  which is a school focused on practical studies for future work applications. Their vision is to help students to be professional learners and to utilise each students full potential. \
\
One thing thats very different from here in Sweden is the fact that the students or apprentices as they are called go in school for 2 days and then work 3 days with their respective profession. That gives the students a unique work experience compared to other schools and gives them a way to ease in to the full work life that will eventually follow. \
\
Working hours\
\
At the Libs the student\'92s have longer days then back in Sweden. The day starts at 7 am and ends at 4 pm. Beyond that they also have shorter breaks adding up to a total of only 55 minutes. That results in 8 hours and 5 minutes of work per day compared to Swedens measly 6 hours and 20 minutes.\
\
Environment\
\
I had my internship at the electrical department of Libs where the students learn about relays, plcs, pneumatics, components, building circuits and so on. Each student gets his/her own workbench with a load out of useful tools like wrenches, screwdrivers and pliers. The students then retrieves the material needed for their project. Everyone works in their own tempo and it was not uncommon to see five people each quietly at their bench working at completely different things.\
\
Hierarchy\
\
The students are guided by mentors who give out and supervises the tasks at hand. They evaluate the students work and verbal presentations of the task is quite common. Whats key here is that the mentors tailors a work plan for every specific student after their individual needs. During the whole education programme there is a few selected categories with assignments that every student have to finish. This can however be done in any order. That way student can have way more authority over what they work with at the moment compared to Sweden.\
\
The fact that the teachers has the title mentors is also reflected in the way they work. You learn by doing and the mentors are more like a guide helping you get back on the right track rather than teaching you straight away. \
\
Gender equality\
\
At the workplace in Birr where I was situated there are no girls taking the automation technician class. This however is not due to any gender rules but rather a lack of interest among girls. \
\
Career possibilities\
\
The education plan at Libs stretches across 4 years the 2 first being work at school and then the 2 last an internship at a company like ABB, Siemens, General Electrics and so on. After the 4 years the students are guaranteed a job in their area of expertise. \
\
