LEAN\
\
Lean is a way of working with a company\'92s effectivity by visualising and eliminating waste. During my stay I  made som observations both good and bad.\
\

\f1\b Good
\f0\b0 \
\
Brakes are very punctual and students honour the schedule.\
\
The students work really intense during work hour and do not slack off or chat with co-workers.\
\
Breaks during the day are very short which increases the time available. The only downside by this is that the students might find it hard to relax during breaks.\
\

\f1\b Bad
\f0\b0 \
\
A really long time is spent on cleaning which does not produce any product. Keeping the workplace organised is very important in lean but because the long time available for cleaning people work in a very slow phase. This could be solved by adding schedules for the different areas that needs to be cleaned to make everyone responsible for a specific task.\
\
There is a lot of tasks with very repetitive work which does not teach the student anything more but just takes time.\
\
\cf6 A lot of the task include follow instructions which there is a lack of assignments including problem solving and working out solutions by yourself. \cf0 \
