	One of the most interesting cultural differences between Sweden and Switzerland quickly turned out to 	simply be the lack of them.\
\
	Switzerland seems to share a lot of the things I always regarded as typical Swedish like avoiding sitting 	next to another person on the buss or train, keeping distance on the platform while waiting and the level of 	politeness when meeting stranger at places like the workplace.\
\
	One big difference however is how accepted smoking is. In Sweden smoking is disregarded by many and 	for those who smoke they have a responsibility to move away from others. In Switzerland smoking is very 	common and it was not uncommon to see somebody taking a smoke at the seat next to you on the station 	causing you to need to move.\
\
	Punctuality when it comes to schedules is also way more important in Switzerland as stated above with the 	breaks. In Sweden it\'92s normal to stop and talk to your friends if you pass them in the hall or maybe sit a 	minute or two extra in the break room to finish a discussion.\
